traffic_visible_response: "Under the Dome" can refer to different works. The more well-known one is the documentary "Under the Dome" by Chai Jing.This documentary is a work that focuses on the issue of smog. In it, Chai Jing uses a combination of data analysis, on-site investigations, and interviews to deeply explore the causes, hazards, and impacts of smog on people's lives and the environment. It also discusses relevant solutions and policy suggestions. The documentary has played a certain role in raising public awareness of environmental protection and promoting discussions on air pollution control.There is also a novel called *Under the Dome* by Stephen King. It is a science fiction and horror novel. The story is set in a small town where a transparent and indestructible dome suddenly descends, isolating the town from the outside world. The novel focuses on the survival and conflicts of the people in the town under the dome, presenting a series of complex human nature and social problems.
